There shall be a fund to be called •Bangladesh Energy Regulatory Commission Fund• and money, as mentioned below shall be deposited in the fund, such as:-
* grant from the Government or statutory body;
* loans borrowed by the Commission;
* fees and charges deposited under this Act; and
* money received from any other source.

Commission shall have all those powers for the purposes of an investigation or proceedings, which are exercised by a Civil Court at the time of trial under the Code of Civil Procedure, such as: •
* to summon a witness and ensure his presence and examination of the witness on oath;
* to detect and present any important document which may be submitted as a document or evidence;
* to collect evidence through an affidavit;
* to call for public record from any court or office;
* to adjourn hearing;
* to ensure presence and absence of the parties; and
* to review the Commission's decisions, directives or orders.

Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, the Commission, by a general or special order, may ask for information on the following matters from any person or licencee for the sake of discharging its duties under this Act, such as:-
* matter related to power generation, and transmission, distribution, purchase, supply and use of energy;
* any other matter prescribed by regulation.

No person shall engage himself in the following business unless he is empowered by a licence or exempted from having it under this Act or any other Act, such as:-
* power generation;
* energy transmission;
* energy distribution and marketing;
* energy supply; and
* energy storage.

At the time of making the policy, the Commission shall take into consideration the following matters, such as:
* Electricity Act, Presidential Order, Rural Electrification Act and DESA Act;
* to harmonize the tariff with the cost of production, transmission, marketing, distribution, supply and storage of energy;
* efficiency, least cost, excellent service, excellent investment;
* consumersâ¢ interest;
* power generation, and transmission, distribution and supply of energy on commercial basis;
* development of national  energy systems planning ; and
* other matters considered necessary by the Commission for the fulfillment of the objectives of this Act.

Restriction under sub-section (1) shall not be applicable to information in the following cases, such as:-
* information relating to smooth functioning and determination of tariff by the Commission;
* information relating to assistance in the functions of the Government under this Act;

Restriction under sub-section (1) shall not be applicable to information in the following cases, such as:-
* information relating to smooth functioning and determination of tariff by the Commission;
* information relating to assistance in the functions of the Government under this Act;
* information relating to the  assistance in the functioning of the Comptroller and Auditor- General under this Act;
* information relating to an investigation about any criminal offence or any criminal proceedings;
* information supplied to any person authorized under Bankruptcy Act, 1997 (Act No. 10 of 1997)for discharging his obligations; and
* information directly related to any civil proceedings that has been filed under this Act or any other Act.
* approval and implementation of the award;
* cancellation or amendment of the award; or
* sending of the award for review of the arbitrator.

Stealing under sub-section (2) shall mean one or more of the following matters separately or jointly:
* if gas or petroleum product is used from anybody without proper approval or instructions of the licencee or in violation of the approved purpose of use, plan or program;
* if gas or petroleum product is allowed for use without approved meter within the purview of this Act or rules made under this Act;
* if a consumer violates the method, or manner of use of gas or petroleum products as specified by directives or methodology or under rules and regulations under this Act or by puncturing or making any change in a pipeline or through bypassing or tampering meter of a consumer; and
* if wastage or misuse, unauthorized use or use beyond the contract or inconsistent use of gas or petroleum product is done or causes any thing to be done or abets in doing the same.

Without affecting the totality of the said power, regulations may be made, on any or all of the following heads:
* convening of meeting of the Commission along with determination of venue, time of holding meeting, and other matters;
* exercise of administrative powers and performance of functions of the Commission;
* pay, allowances and conditions of services of the officers and employees of the Commission.
* determination of functions of the licencee and persons exempted under this Act;
* making of different codes and standards  ;
* powers, functions, duties and responsibilities of licencee;
* purchase procedures and rules to be followed by the licencee;
* methods of determination of revenue, tariff of the licencee;
* Procedure for renewal, amendment and cancellation of licence
* determination of procedure  relating to maintenance of accounts and forms of the Commission;
* procedure, conditions and other matters in respect of issuance of licence for the production, transmission, distribution, storage and supply of energy;
* procedure determining supply of information by the licencee; and
* policy for giving preference to the supply of energy produced at least cost.

Notwithstanding any thing contained in this Act, the Government shall have the powers for issuing provisional licence subject to the condition consistent with the provisions of this Act, for the production, transmission, storage, distribution and supply of energy for a period not exceeding twelve months from the date on which the Act comes into force, such as: -
* each of the temporary licence issued by the Government shall be submitted to the Commission, which the Commission shall consider as an application for licence under this Act;
* validity of each temporary licence shall be ceased on the date as to be determined by the Commission in the application mentioned in clause (a).
